Package com.opatomic

Class WaitCallbackSF<R,​E>

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.opatomic.WaitCallbackSF<R,​E>
  • Type Parameters:
    R - Object type for result
    E - Object type for error
    All Implemented Interfaces:
    CallbackSF<R,​E>
    public class WaitCallbackSF<R,​E>
extends Object
implements CallbackSF<R,​E>
    A callback that helps make a request synchronous by waiting for response. Example usage: 
     
   WaitCallbackSF<Object,Object> wcb = new WaitCallbackSF<Object,Object>();
   client.call("PING", null, wcb);
   wcb.waitIfNotDone();
   if (wcb.error != null) {
     // error occurred
   } else {
     // no error, result is stored in wcb.result
   }
   // can re-use wcb by calling reset()
   client.call("PING", null, wcb.reset());
   wcb.waitIfNotDone();
   // ... check wcb.error/wcb.result ...
